<font color="#FF0000">TO DR SPATZ</font><br>
<tt>Sun Dec 15 23:22:05 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
Dr Spatz,<br><br>
I am a veteran of the Vietnam War. I was drafted as a young man. <br><br>
I knew 2 CO's who served there as Army medics. One was very badly wounded.<br><br>
Why they served, instead of choosing jail, as you did is anyone's guess. <br><br>
I am willing to bet that they were ignored when they returned home just as those of us who &quot;partook&quot; in the actual killing were. <br><br>
When you call us &quot;whiners&quot; you lose the objectivity a doctor should have. Is that how you administer treatment to your patients? Do you call them names? <br><br>
There is a legitimate need for Veterans to talk about the war. Not to justify the war, but rather to tell of the horror. There will always be people like you who claim to be RIGHT. <br><br>
What is important is a rapprochement of the American people. This can be attained through thoughtful discussion.<br><br>
Do you want me to say that the war was wrong? Yes, in my opinion it was. Having said that, I will tell you that your self righteous attitude will forever prevent any coming together of the people of this country. So in that respect how right are you?<br><br>

<p><code>-- wingman@greene.xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


